    "We first argue that Grice's original maxims (quantity, quality, relevance, and manner) -with some rephrasing to improve their prescriptiveness -are necessary in human-AI conversations.",
    "We then assert that two new maxims, benevolence and transparency, are essential in addressing some of the shortcomings inherent to current human-AI interactions.",
    "Throughout the discussion of the maxims, the reader is directed to Appendix A for example conversations that illustrate the violations.",
